HEADWORD: Acroamatical
<hw>Ac`ro*a*mat"ic*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to hear.]</ety> <def>Communicated orally; oral;
-- applied to the <xex>esoteric</xex> teachings of Aristotle, those
intended for his genuine disciples, in distinction from his
<xex>exoteric</xex> doctrines, which were adapted to outsiders or the
public generally. Hence: Abstruse; profound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acroatic</ent>⟦br⟧
